     <section class="project-detail-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>OSM and JOSM data session</h1>
            <img src="Projects other/JOSM+OSM.png" alt="Project 1 Image" class="img-fluid">
            <h2>Summary</h2>
            <p>The process of uploading, editing, and modifying data in JOSM (Java OpenStreetMap Editor) to the OpenStreetMap (OSM) platform is a vital component of community mapping initiatives. This involves training sessions aimed at familiarizing mappers with the concepts and techniques of data management and editing using JOSM, while also highlighting the importance of contributing to OSM for various purposes, such as disaster response, urban planning, and environmental conservation. Also uploading data from KRCS ICHA team to OSM to make it open source.</p>
            
            <h1>Mathare Disaster Risk Reduction</h1>
            <img src="Projects other/DRR.png" alt="Project 1 Image" class="img-fluid">
            <h2>Summary</h2>
            <p>The Mathare Disaster Risk Reduction (DRR) initiative, a collaborative effort between the Kenya Red Cross Society (KRCS) and Nairobi County, focuses on identifying and mitigating fire risk areas within the Mathare community. This project aims to enhance the community's resilience to fire disasters by conducting comprehensive assessments to pinpoint vulnerable areas prone to fire outbreaks. Through careful analysis of various factors such as population density, infrastructure, and environmental conditions, the initiative aims to create a detailed portfolio of high-risk zones. </p>
            
            <h1>Garissa Farms Drone images</h1>
            <img src="Projects other/DRONE.png" alt="Project 1 Image" class="img-fluid">
            <h2>Summary</h2>
            <p>The Garissa Farms Image Mapping project, conducted in collaboration with local authorities and disaster response agencies, focuses on documenting and analyzing the use of farms as temporary camps during the El Niño phenomenon. By utilizing satellite imagery and geographic information systems (GIS), this initiative aims to create detailed maps illustrating the spatial distribution of these makeshift camps across Garissa County. Through meticulous analysis of the terrain, land use patterns, and infrastructure, the project seeks to identify areas where farming lands were utilized as shelters during the El Niño events</p>
          </div>
